# HRMS Coding Standards

## General

- Use English for all code, comments, variable names
- PascalCase: Classes, Methods, Properties, Enums
- camelCase: variables, parameters
- Keep methods under 50 lines
- Single responsibility principle

## Backend (.NET 8)

### Naming
- Interfaces: I[Entity]Repository
- Commands: [Action][Entity]Command
- Queries: [Action][Entity]Query
- Handlers: [Action][Entity]Handler

### Structure
- One class per file
- Namespace matches folder structure
- usings at top, sorted

### Error Handling
- Use try-catch in handlers
- Return proper ApiResponse with error
- Log exceptions

## Frontend (Angular)

### Components
- Standalone components only
- Use @if, @for instead of *ngIf, *ngFor
- Signals for state management

### Naming
- Components: [feature]-[component].component.ts
- Services: [feature].service.ts
- Interfaces: [feature].model.ts
